						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Undated. In <hi rend="italic">Vaṭṭeḻuttu</hi> characters. (8th cent. A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that the image was that of Kaṉakavīrap Periyaḍigaḷ, a disciple of Guṇasēṉadēvar, who was a disciple of Ashṭa-upavāsi Bhaṭārar of Kuṟaṇḍi, a village in Veṇbu-nāḍu. The image was carved on behalf of the villagers of Amirthapākkirama Nallūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kuyiṟkuḍi in Nāṭṭāṟṟppuram. It is stated that the image shall be protected by the monks of the Jaina monastery <hi rend="italic">(paḷḷi).</hi></p>						

						</summary>
